@node Information "Information"
This program simply opens an ANSI screen and allows commands to be typed
in at the command prompt. In effect it opens a shell on an ANSI screen.

I made this program because I like to use the shell for fiddling around
with CLI BBS game doors, for instance logging on locally to hack'n'slash
and similar. I needed to play these games in ANSI so I could see the
colours.

I couldn't find a program which did it, so I made my own. This has taken
me several months, as I have had to learn how to program in Amiga E
first :)
@endnode
@node Installation "Installation"
Use the supplied installer script to install the program (this uses the
standard Commodore installer program).

If you wish to install the program manually then you must copy the IBM
font and associated directory to FONTS: and copy the program and it's
documentation anywhere you like.
@endnode
@node Usage "Usage"
This program is simply run from either it's icon, or from the CLI. No
arguments are needed. A black & red coloured screen will open and you
will be able to type text into into like a normal shell.

To exit the program type `EndCli' at the prompt. Like a normal shell, if
you enter a command which doesn't return to the shell prompt, then you
will not be able to close the window by typing `EndCli'.
@endnode
